The Facility has procedures in place, including both on-site activities and coordination with off-site responders that are to be followed in the event of a butane release.



STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES HANDLED



The Facility receives by pipeline and stores butane mixtures in underground storage caverns. The regulated flammable chemicals stored at the Facility include Refinery Grade Butane (a flammable mixture containing ethane, propane, isobutane, n-butane, isopentane, and n-pentane) and n-butane (a flammable mixture containing n-butane, pentane, and isobutane).  The Facility also stores a small quantity of propane (500 gallons); however, the propane is used as fuel for an on-site flare and is not RMP-regulated.  



The Facility has two underground storage caverns that may contain either n-butane or Refinery Grade Butane, one of which is capable of storing 1,773,479 barrels of product, and the other of which is capable of storing 1,562,855 barrels of product.  



GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS



